Eco-Bat Technologies Reports 30% Jump in First Quarter Profit

-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 
2011-05-27T06:30:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/eco-bat-technologies-reports-30-jump-in-first-quarter-profit.html
Eco-Bat Technologies Ltd. , the
largest lead producer in  Europe  and  South Africa , reported a 30
percent jump in first-quarter profit.  Net income rose to 44 million pounds ($72 million) in the
three months ended March 31 from 33.9 million pounds in the same
period last year, the Matlock, England-based company said in an
e-mailed report today. Revenue jumped 21 percent to almost 484.8
million pounds.  Lead for delivery in three months averaged 15 percent
higher over the period, and was at $9,095.25 a metric ton at
6:48 a.m. in London. Eco-Bat sold 220,000 tons of lead in the
first three months this year, up from 216,000 tons a year
earlier, the company said.  ((Eco-Bat will hold a conference call at 2 p.m. U.K. time.
